An Oredo Magistratesâ€™ Court in Edo State has sentenced Mr. David Oteme, 23, to six months imprisonment for stealing. David was arraigned alongside Shamsu Aliu and Farouk Sani on five-count charge of stealing goods worth thousands of naira. He pleaded guilty to count one bordering on conspiracy and stealing, but pleaded not guilty to other charges. Shamsu and Farouk pleaded not guilty to the four-count charge preferred against them. David was alleged to have broken into a provision store belonging to Odion Ukachukwu where he carted away drinks worth N62, 500 and also stole N557,000 burglary proof of Emotan Primary School. The case was adjourned till April 30.